[normal]Supplementary [bold]written evidence submitted by HM Government (GHS[bold]0019)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Please find below the membership list regarding the governance structures around the Horizon Scanning Programme which I’m happy to be included as written evidence. The CoI
[normal] table has been updated since you last saw it. Sorry for the delay, but I was off sick and only just returned to work.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]▪
[normal]              
[normal]The 
[normal]CSAG[bold] is: The Cabinet Secretary, Sir Bob Kerslake (CLG), Martin Donnelly (BIS), Chris Wormald (DfE), Simon Fraser (FCO), Sir Mark W
[normal]alport (GCSO), Matthew Rycroft (HMT), Mark Lowcock (DfID), Jil Matheson (UKSA/ONS), Bernard Gray (MoD), Jon Day (CO), Robert Devereux (DWP), and Una O’Brien (DH).
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]▪
[normal]              
[normal]The 
[normal]GOSH[bold] is: Cabinet Office, BIS, CPNI, DCLG, DECC, DEFRA, DFID, DfT, DH, DWP, DfE, FCO, G
[normal]CHQ, GO Science, HMRC, HMT, HO, MoJ, MoD, NSS, ONS, NCA, Government Actuaries Dept. and the Devolved Administrations. (20+ government organisations as some departments also have agency representation)
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]▪
